description: Late 18th century Dorset British slang for confused, bewildered.  From be- +‎ twattle (“to talk”) +‎ -ed.

adjectives.description: betwattled (comparative more betwattled, superlative most betwattled)

entries.meaning: (archaic, West Country) surprised, confounded, befuddled, to be in a distressed state of mind.
(archaic) simple past tense and past participle of betwattle
